  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (09d53c2 2022-03-31T00:31:39.994883040+00:00)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test --debug\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n`forge test --debug` does not respect the `--use` flag and instead tries to redownload the solc binary via svm-rs (which are currently not compatible with nixos: https://github.com/roynalnaruto/svm-rs/issues/36):\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ export SOLC=/nix/store/q72kbq1kl03jhpyv04zv29d0kv67gczk-solc-static-0.8.10/bin/solc-0.8.10\r\n\r\n$ forge test --use $SOLC\r\n[⠊] Compiling...\r\n[⠔] Compiling 3 files with 0.8.10\r\nCompiler run successful\r\n\r\n$ forge test --use $SOLC --debug testExample\r\n[⠊] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n[⠊] Compiling...\r\n[⠔] installing solc version \"0.8.10\"\r\n[⠒] Successfully installed solc 0.8.10\r\nError:\r\n   0: \"/home/me/.svm/0.8.10/solc-0.8.10\": No such file or directory (os error 2)\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli/src/cmd/utils.rs:118\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n```",
